## 4. DecisionAgent — Rule-Based Decision Specialist

**Module**: [decision/](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision)

| Function | File | What it computes |
|:---|:---|:---|
| [build_kpi_contract()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py#64-136) | [kpi_contract.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py) | Assembles CHA + DHA + Economics KPIs into one canonical contract |
| [decide_from_contract()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py#82-239) | [rules.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py) | **The core decision**: feasibility gate → cost comparison → MC robustness → CO₂ tiebreaker |
| [validate_config()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py#24-65) | [rules.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py) | Validates decision thresholds (cost tolerance, win fractions) |
| `ContractValidator.validate()` | [schemas.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/schemas.py) | Validates KPI contract schema completeness |
| [_infer_dh_feasibility()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py#242-260) | [kpi_contract.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py) | Infers DH feasibility from CHA convergence + EN 13941-1 compliance |
| [_infer_hp_feasibility()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py#261-277) | [kpi_contract.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py) | Infers HP feasibility from DHA violation counts |
| [_infer_dh_reasons()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py#278-303) / [_infer_hp_reasons()](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py#304-336) | [kpi_contract.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py) | Generates reason codes (e.g. `COST_DH_CHEAPER`, `HP_VOLTAGE_VIOLATIONS`) |

**Decision logic (deterministic, never LLM)**:
1. If only one option is feasible → pick it
2. If costs differ >5% → pick cheaper
3. If costs are close → use Monte Carlo robustness (≥70% wins = robust)
4. CO₂ tiebreaker if still tied

**Answerable questions**: *"Which is better, DH or HP?", "Why was DH recommended?", "Is the decision robust?"*

