## Summary: The Answerability Boundary

```
User question
    │
    ▼
NLU classifies intent ──────────────────────── UNKNOWN? → CapabilityGuardrail
    │                                                         "I can't do that"
    ▼
Executor picks agent plan
    │
    ▼
Agents run their functions ◄── THIS IS THE BOUNDARY
    │                          If a function exists → answerable
    ▼                          If no function exists → blocked
Results returned to UI
```

> **Bottom line**: The system can answer any question that ultimately requires computing something from the functions listed above. Everything else is explicitly blocked by the [CapabilityGuardrail](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/agents/fallback.py#44-335) with graceful fallback.
